<desilva@med.unc.edu>
[The GIDEON database offers no information about endemic typhus in Sri
Lanka, but does suggest that the disease is commoner in warmer climates.
Endemic typhus is maintained in a rat/flea cycle, and rodent control is key
to controlling the disease in humans. Unless drought brings rats into
closer contact with humans, I can think of no reason to relate the 2
events. Presumptive laboratory diagnosis using simple serological tests
should be within the capability of most hospital laboratories. Additional
information would be appreciated. - Mod.ES]
..........................es/pg/sh
